        "timestamp": "2021-01-24 02:10:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nOverall it looks good. However, I'd like you write a separate jira to fix this coding style issue:\n\n\nNever use catch-all except: statements, or catch Exception or StandardError, unless you are\n\nre-raising the exception, or\ncreating an isolation point in the program where exceptions are not propagated but are recorded and suppressed instead, such as protecting a thread from crashing by guarding its outermost block.\n\nSee https://google.github.io/styleguide/pyguide.html for more information on the use of exceptions in python code.\n\nPlease respond with the Jira ticket number for that.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8d5fb38b1262daf1bb139e9a630e1f49fba96605",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4405,
          "name": "Fiachra Corcoran",
          "display_name": "Fiachra Corcoran (EST)",
          "email": "fiachra.corcoran@est.tech",
          "username": "efiacor"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-01-25 09:36:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Overall it looks good. However, I'd like you write a separate jira to fix this coding style issue:\n> \n> \n> Never use catch-all except: statements, or catch Exception or StandardError, unless you are\n> \n> re-raising the exception, or\n> creating an isolation point in the program where exceptions are not propagated but are recorded and suppressed instead, such as protecting a thread from crashing by guarding its outermost block.\n> \n> See https://google.github.io/styleguide/pyguide.html for more information on the use of exceptions in python code.\n> \n> Please respond with the Jira ticket number for that.\n\nHi Tony,\n\nI agree it's probably not ideal but could you point to where you see the problem you describe? In the sub_handler.execute method?\n\nJira created here - https://jira.onap.org/browse/DCAEGEN2-2589",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "e9fad85a0c1f74b9de35ecfa191981c7109be437",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4405,
          "name": "Fiachra Corcoran",
